The United States greatly appreciates their efforts and transparency."
The United States paid $400 million to the WHO for 2018-2019, according to the organization's website.
Trump said he would "channel" the money into other areas to combat the coronavirus outbreak.
"Halting funding for the World Health Organization during a world health crisis is as dangerous as it sounds," Bill Gates tweeted.
Monday, as Trump showed a promotional video praising his handling of the coronavirus outbreak, he said, "Everything we did was right."